# MenuOS — Core Context

**Product:** Premium SaaS QR menu platform for restaurants, hotels, beach bars, pool bars, room service, spa menus.

**Customers:** B2B = business owner (signup, subscription, dashboard). B2C = guest scans QR (no app, mobile web only).

**Domain:** `menuos.gr` (production). Staging: `staging.menuos.gr` (future).

**Three surfaces:** (1) Marketing/SaaS site, (2) Owner/Staff dashboard, (3) Public QR menu (`menuos.gr/m/{venue}`).

**Multi-tenant:** Every query scoped by `organizationId`. Each business has venues → menus → categories → items.

**Hard rules:**
- No AI anywhere. OCR = Tesseract + rule-based parsing only (Phase 3).
- Call waiter = WebSocket + Web Push (PWA). No native iOS/Android app.
- Premium UI: Blue/cyan gradient (#2563EB / #06B6D4), Manrope, QR+M logo. Tagline: Scan. Browse. Enjoy.
- **Never touch MatchWork or other servers** without explicit user approval. MenuOS deploys to `/opt/menuos` only.
- Local development first; production deploy only when user approves.

**Stack:** Next.js 15 (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind + shadcn/ui · PostgreSQL 16 + Prisma · NextAuth v5 · Socket.io · Cloudflare R2 · Stripe (Phase 2) · Python FastAPI OCR service (Phase 3).

